<br>
EQ has progressed into a game with more emphasis on &quot;access to player resources&quot;.<br>
<br>
Where once it was a game which provided you with base abilities at each level given only a commitment of time, it now limits access to certain base abilities at each level based upon your access to the specific &quot;player resources&quot; set as hurdles to acquire them.<br>
<br>
Zone access, spell access, equipment access etc,; it's not just a simple, generic XP timesink to acquire anymore.<br>
<br>
Now you have to be able to group with specific class/levels, raid with specific groups, etc.<br>
<br>
It is a game that has become very focused on social connections.<br>
<br>
Recognize that the game has changed, and find out if what it is now is really what you want in it.<br>
<br>
Fortunately, there will be many alternatives arriving shortly, and perhaps one of these will have more of the focus you enjoy.<br>
<br>
As a side note, you may just want to sit out for a bit or pick up an alt.<br>
I expect that some of these &quot;growing pains&quot; will work themselves out as more content is farmed.<br>
Quests are figured out and spoilers written.<br>
Spells/Songs farmed and excesses left on Mules at lower and lower rates.<br>
<br>
It does seem that the player community has bad attitudes for the few posters that wasted my time in reading there comments.<br>
They may not have gotten anything from your post, but they obviously employed no intelligence whatsoever in thinking we needed to hear them express themselves for who knows why. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andraelarcaneumrunner>Andrael Arcaneumrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Hand Of<BR>The Cabal (tm)!!!</span><br>  Posts: 1328<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/30/02 9:32:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm53.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Finally had enough of EQ . . bye bye</span><hr size=1> /agree...well written reply.<br>
